In [33]:
# Alternative/ Object oriented way to plot figure
fig = plt.figure()

axes = fig.add_axes([0.1,0.1,0.8,0.8])

axes.plot(x,y,label='sin(X)')
axes.set_xlabel('X')
axes.set_ylabel('sin(x)')
axes.set_title('Sine Function')
axes.legend()

plt.show()
